Communicated by:
Ronan Kelly for FluTrackers.com
<ronankelly@comcast.net>

[The one additional death cited in the report in [1] above has
occurred in the past 24 hours (see ProMED-mail archive no 20110913.2793). Presumably this case is also due to JE virus
infection, as yesterday's (13 Sep 2011) report indicated that the 24
deaths were due to infection by that virus.

There are no indications given about the measures to be taken to halt
the spread of the disease. Is a JE virus vaccination campaign planned?
Again, the etiology of the acute encephalitis syndrome cases in the
Muzaffarpur district mentioned above is not specified.

Gaya is the 2nd largest city in Bihar state and the capital of the
district. A HealthMap Interactive map showing the location of Gaya can
be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1emt.

With respect to the information in report [2] above, JE cases are
widely scattered across the Indian states. It would be of interest to
know if vaccination campaigns were carried out in the states most
affected. - Mod.TY]
